\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I can't say. I were married. Because I went to stay up with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 About how long would you have been married do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I think me children about either seven or eight. Me two girls, you know, I have two girls. And this is grandchild - one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 That gives us an approximate idea of how old your father would be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. He was seventy. On the Sunday as we buried him on the Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 And this would be some time in the late 1930's?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. Must have been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you know where he came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Yes. He came from - Scopey Lane - they called it Labbys Farm. It was but you see they've built down there since now so they call it Timberbottom down that way. Yes, yes
. But it was over that water now whether they've filled that water in I don't know - and there were little narrow bridges you went to this farm. Then me grandma brought nine up on that farm. Yes. They called it Labby's Farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your father work first of all in the bleach works or did he have a job before that do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well he were a - a labourer I think like when he went to work for me grandma.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 On the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, I think he worked mostly there like and then I think he got a job labouring you know. From what I gather off -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You think he started off on the farm and did he then go to the bleach works?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh no. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 He'd have another labouring job in between?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, yes. But I don't really know what because she give all her other sons - trades, you know, but me dad wouldn't have a trade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 So as far as you personally can remember he was first of all in the bleach works?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, and then he worked for - Turton Urban District and he worked for - John Willie Warburton at Affetside as a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Painter and decorator?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well he wasn't but he was a labourer for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 He was labouring all his life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. More or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did he have a job after working....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 After me mum died he stopped at home - he didn't work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What was his last job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Eeh, I forget. Whether he were on Turton Urban District then, I think so, I'm not sure. But he used to go on farms and hay make and do all that you know when it were hay making, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 He in fact didn't have a settled job at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 He was labouring for this body and that body?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Different ones. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 So in effect a lot of the work he was doing would be called casual work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did he have any part time jobs in addition to his full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Oh no. No. Oh, may - when it were hay making time he'd go and help farms as he knew. You know. Yes. Yes. Like he worked for Turton Urban District and then like he'd go and do that like at Saturday and - nights, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you remember him ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Well, they were out of work you know when weather be bad because used to have shocking winters then and - and they only got about eighteen bob a week when they were working a week, you know.
 But they used to be out of work with frost because we used to have a lot, you know. The cold winters and snow then. Oh, it were wicked. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1995576\charrsid2687195 
They don't know half of winters now as we had because I gave to me work with clogs - we wore clogs then you know - and 
we've had stocking tops and we slurred down to weaving shed down the Blew - down to Ashworth's weaving in what they called Ashworth's Bottoms. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
I don't know whether you know it or not but there's a school - what do they call that school - Cannon Slade is it - at - visit doctors there - well, like }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1995576\charrsid2687195 Sherwood\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195  Farm up the Oaks Lane where me dad used to go and work for, well you went straight over railway to this weaving shed and right down. I don't know whether there's anything there now because I've not been r
ound and the ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oaks Lane is built on I know that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Oh, I know all the houses is built up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you know how old your mother would be when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Eeh no, I don't. I couldn't - I couldn't say. 'Cos me mam was sixty-si
x when she died and she - and me dad lived ten years and a month after her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Bradshaw. Yes. I don't know whether you knew }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1995576\charrsid2687195 the smithy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195  in - well, it's Harwood, they call it Harwood - it's just over border from Crofters, you
 know, it's Harwood really. But there was a smithy, a Conservative club and a smithy underneath. Do you know it at all? Well, the house has stood next to the smithy on its own - me grandma lived there. Well it's been altered now - a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your mother have any jobs before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, she did work but - I heard her once say she worked at - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
Street}}Cakenbolton Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} over }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1995576\charrsid2687195 Breightment}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195  way - she used to help a lady there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was she in domestic service then before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, not r
eally - I don't know whether she was a weaver or not - I could never say so. But I've heard her talk about this - working there - over {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Oakenbolton Road{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did she work after she was married at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. She used to wash - for people. You know, she used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 In her own home or did she go out to ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Yes, yes. No. She - she only went to Lisa Tootal's in Turton Road - but one time we lived there - up Turton Road when I were little going to school and - her father was our landlord, who lived 
in a little single house up there. That was only place she ever went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did she work at all after the children were born - did she still go on washing for people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, she washed at home for people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 She didn't go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, no. 'Course a lot didn't go out then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How many rooms were there in the house at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}King Street
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 There - two up and two down for anything I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would it be two bedrooms upstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I'm just wondering because you see there were some single houses. N
ow whether it were a single house we lived in I don't know. 'Cos I don't remember the - at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Which is the house you do remember best when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Er - well, I remember that one in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Lee Gate Lane
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} but it was when the back - that were a single house before we went into the house in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Lee Gate Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 The house you went in first in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Lee Gate Lane{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} was a single house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, that was a single house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What do you mean by that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Why, it were one up and one down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How many of you lived there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well - well I think we'd all live there because we went -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You and your two brothers - you were all born then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes. Yes. Because - we moved from there into {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Lee Gate Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} in the double house you see when our Tom went working full time. Because the house rent was only three and nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 This was the first house in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Lee Gate Lane{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, the second one. Two up two down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 The first house, one up and one down you'd be a bit crowded wouldn't you? Was there anybody els
e at all besides your parents you're your brothers and yourself living there - you didn't have -?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. And me grandmother lived across road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your mother have anybody to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. Never. Not 'til I grew up you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your mother or father mend or make any of the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh, me mam used to make our - mine like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 But not the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did she mend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. She had to do. 'Cos we didn't get a big wage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 The clothes that were bought - were they new?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 They were always new?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Mm. More or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were they sometimes not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, I remember having one or two things cut down and made to fit me. Because I 
used to be friendly with them at the Post Office, now they had girls and they worked at - well, as they grew older Fanny worked at - Post Office in town - general - and they used to give me clothes and I had them cut down and made to fit, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 The clothes that were bought.....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 They were always new.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were they bought in town or where?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes. They were bought in town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Any particular shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No. She used to go just anywhere - where she wanted to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What about shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh well, I used to go - I remember going to Morris's in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Market Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} at one time. I don't know whether there's anybody living along of them now. I don't know whether it's not {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Tylers{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did all the family get their shoes from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, I think they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your father ever mend your shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
No, I don't think so. I think we used to take them to Jack Bridges at Bradshaw Chapel. That's - yes. That is - where you turn round it was - a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1995576\charrsid2687195 shoe shop}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195  and he used to mend clogs and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, not really. Because he was always doing some jobs outside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did he ever do anything like cleaning or cooking or washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would he make the fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh he may do that because, you know, at that time - they used to rake in winter times, you know, and all that fires -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Keep it in all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your father do any of the decorating or repairs or improvements or anything to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No. All - it belonged to the crofters - the croft used to do it all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did he do anything for you as children like dressing or undressing or bathing you. Not as I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did he ever read to you or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No, he wasn't a reader, me dad, but he had a good memory.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did he take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Or look after you when she went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, she never went out a great lot not them days they didn't. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you yourself have any tasks to carry out regularly at home to help your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, I used to wait for washing and ironing and take them back to ladies where they had to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you do any other jobs besides that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well I used to do mopping and all that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was this your regular responsibility?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Mm. And I used to go out shopping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How long did you go on doing these things - 'til after you left school? or 'til you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well my - me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1995576\charrsid2687195 mother were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195  dead when I got married. I was about twenty-nine when I got married. And did most of work you know like when I were working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 So you went on doing a lot of housework after you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes. And I looked after them after me mum died you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your brothers have any jobs to do when they were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 They used - our Fred used to come with me - errands you know and that. No, they used to go fishing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did the older children have to help the younger ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 With anything like dressing or feeding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, no. Me mam used to look after us. She were a good mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did the younger children help the older ones at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, we were - yes - we were always in bed early. Well, I've gone to bed at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}half past eight{\*\xmlclose}
 when I were working. Because there wasn't a lot, you know, going on them days. Not in the country, you know, you had to go to town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you were going to school what time did you have to go to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh, want to bed early. Used to be all in bed by ten - when we were working. We were never out of bed any of us late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What time did you go to bed as children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh we had to go to bed early - me mam made us, you know, about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname 
Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose}. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your mother or anybody else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Not even when you were very small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. Only me mother. Me mother looked after us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How old would you be when you started to put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I couldn't say. 'Cos we used to go if we were tired, you know, we'd go upstairs and we didn't bother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How old would you be when you started doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Eeh, I don't think I know. I can't go back, you know. Can't go back -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you share the bedroom or the bed with anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No, I had a bed of me own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What about the bedroom - would there be other beds in the bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. The boys slept in the other room with me father and mother and I had the other room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What about when you were in the house with only one room upstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well they had - we were all small then, you know, and we all slept - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How many beds would there be there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh there were one - single bed you know and like a - a bigger one for the boys and then there were me mothers and fathers. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 So there were three beds in that one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Yes, yes. 'Course they used to - they used to say, now whether it were correct, but one time they used to have round beds, you know, when they had these big families.
 'Course we'd only three of us. But they said they used to have these single beds - you know, single houses and they used to all have a - a round bed they used to say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Have you any reason to suppose that this was true?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well I don't really know -
 I don't. Because, you know, they did have big families. Yes. But I never saw any. But I have heard 'em say some slept at feet, you know, I could take that in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Which room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, me mother used to have a big tin bath, you know, great big one and we used to have it at front of fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You'd only one room downstairs hadn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, that were all, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How often did the various members of the family bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, we always had a - a bath like at Friday night. Every week. Yes, Every week. And then we used to have good washes, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 But was it just the one night the bath was got out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, as we had the bath, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh well, me mother used to keep u
s clean, she used to wash practically every day you know. She were very particular over clothes - very. Like she said, we weren't well off but we had clean clothes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Where did you have your meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 In the living room. Yes. Oh there were no kitchens like they do now you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, you'd just this one room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. 'Course we - we did have a work in the back kitchen and we used to have our food in the living room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 This was when you'd moved into the other house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 But when you were in the one with only one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, we had to do - yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Where did your mother cook - obviously it would be in the one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Well, they used to cook a lot on the fire, you know, because they had a oven attached to 
the - fireplace you know. And they used to put it down and they cooked with a big pan to make broth, you know. And then cooked their bread and all that in the oven. They made all their own bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you had the two rooms was the coal fire and the oven in the living room or the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. No, in the living room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your mother have any other cooking equipment like a gas stove of any kind or a gas range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, I don't think we had any then. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you were a child what time was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well we had to go to school you know for nine so it were between eight and nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Which members of the family would be present then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well we were all three - Tom, Fred and me. And me mother. And me dad went out, you know, early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How did he manage for his breakfast - did he get it himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, me mother used to put it up and they used to have it you know when they were outside working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 He didn't have a meal before he went out then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well he had a drink 
and something to eat you know and then he'd take his breakfast with him. And his dinner he'd get if she - me mother hadn't made him one to take. 'Course working outside it were hard work to warm 'em you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What did you usually have to eat and drink for your breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Well, it just depended what me mother had. But at one time you know it'd be a lot of porridge we used to get and we'd have eggs - 'cos eggs used to be cheap then, and bananas you know. 'Cos you could get them very che
ap. And they they'd buy bacon - and eggs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you have anything special on Sundays for instance or did you still have your porridge?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh no, we used to have - bacon and egg and we used to have meat and all like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 For breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Like at Sunday. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What about the mid-day meal - what time would you you're your mid-day meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, we used to come home from school, you know, at twelve and me mother always had our food ready - always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was it a cooked meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. Always cooked us something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What would you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Well, it just depended what time she had. She'd sometimes make potato pie, sometimes a meat pie, sometimes she'd make steak puddings and - sometimes it would be tater hash and a pudding, you know, we used to get a pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you have something to drink as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, we'd have a drink of tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was that what you had to drink at breakfast as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you have a special Sunday dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, we always had our Sunday dinner - we always had roast meat. And }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1995576\charrsid2687195 
potato}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195  and all that you know, vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What about the evening meal - did you call it tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. We always had to have tea - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What time did you have your tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Round about half past four to five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Who would be present then - would it be the children and your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, or me dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would he be back from work then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What sort of a meal would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well it just depended what she'd got, you know, lik
e - do you mean on a Sunday? Through the week. Well, if she could get black pudding sometimes she'd get them for me dad because he liked 'em. And on a Monday they used to have mussels and cockles and all like that, you know, and fish and she'd get pork st
eaks, you know, and do onions with 'em. Oh we - we were well looked after. Oh me mam were a good cook - oh yes, she was a good cook me mam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you have tea again to drink at teatime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Oh, it wasn't much coffee or anything. But I used to go r
ound with the milk at one time and there were Tom and all - well, we used to get a pint of milk. And then there were butter milk you know as we got cheap them days. And we used to drink a lot of buttermilk, you know, but I didn't like milk on its own - ne
ver did. And I don't now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would you have the buttermilk at odd times during the day or at meal times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No - like when it were warm weather they mostly came round with buttermilk. 'Course milk were cheaper then than what it is today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you have that instead of tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Most - most - if you wanted it you could have it you know because tea were dearer really to buy but still it were cheap to what it is now.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you have a supper before you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well if you were hungry me mother'd let you had a - either a piece of cake or a - piece of bread and jam, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you have a drink then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, sometimes. If you wanted one you could have a drink of milk. Because - we used to get milk, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You say your mother baked her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did she make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I couldn't say whether she did that or not because we could get jam cheap then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did she bottle any fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, I don't really know. I know we used to have fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Can you remember if she made pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh well, they used to cook onions up and do, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did she make any wine or medicine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh I remember her making beetroot wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What about medicines? Did she make any hero remedies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh, me grandma did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 But not your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Not that I know of. Me grandma used to brew herbs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was there any beer brewed for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your father and mother grow and vegetables and fruit themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, they had no garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did they buy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 It were cheap then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was it always fresh fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did they sometimes buy tinned or dried?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh sometimes she'd have a tinned fruit but - she always had fresh fruit.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 There wasn't a garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. But as our Fred grew up he had a garden and he grew his own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 But your parents didn't have a garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did they keep any livestock anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Our Food used to have a rabbit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 While he was at home in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 As a pet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I was thinking more of things like hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You know, food }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1995576\charrsid2687195 producing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. He used to grow tomatoes when he had his garden and all that you know, beans and peas and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 But this wasn't when he was at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
No, 'til he grew up. Oh yes, he were in family - he weren't married - not then. He weren't married. Yes. He had a big greenhouse and a garden. Like over King Street side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I thought you meant that when he got married and moved into a house where there was a garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, he didn't get married 'til late on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 As the family was growing up there was this source of your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes. And lettuce and reddish and - young onions and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Eeh, I couldn't say because me mother used to send for meat nearly every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you ever get any extra meat such as rabbit from somebody poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, our Fred.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did he poach?
