\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you have anything special to eat on your birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Me mother might have made a jelly, you know, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you have any friends in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I had when I were twenty-one-war were on. I had a potato pie supper, you know when I were twenty-one. And war were on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Can you remember how you spent Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, it were - we used to get a few toffees and - orange and apple and - perhaps me grandma would give me a threepenny bit but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you spend the day at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Or did you join with other relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh no, we always - no, we always stayed home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Just your own family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you have any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was there anybody who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. Well me mother used 
to do and - perhaps a neighbour would come, in at Christmas Eve and he used to sing with her - here "high" again the fire and more often than -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You were saying more often than not it was Holy, Holy, Holy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Holy, you know, at Christmas time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your parents play any games with you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, they'd no time them days - not with hard work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I suppose so and we had the Bible you know, but - I didn't read like then like I do now; And then there weren't money to buy books really.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you have newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, we had a paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What would it be - a local paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. The Evening News.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What about magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, we used to come round with the church magazine, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was that the only one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you remember your mother or father reading - you you're your father didn't read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, he wasn't a reader.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 She'd let me read to her - she liked me reading to her. As I grew up, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did she ever read aloud to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Not - not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Or to your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you remember there being a funeral in the family when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No, I can't remember me granddad and me grandma being buried.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were you taken out visiting neighbours or friends or relatives at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Oh yes, she - me mother used to take us to me grandmother and we used to stay with her mother at Saturday nights while me other auntie went ou
t when we were little. Because you see she were wed - her husband died you know - but I don't remember his funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your mother take you anywhere else - to friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, she used to take us like to different ones and relations.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would this be fairly often or only now and again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh no, now and then because she had work to do you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were you taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, I used to go in town with me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you go with anybody else or just your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, not '
til I grew up, I used to go with my mother 'til I grew up like. And then I went out with that lady. Oh, I went out with her a while. But she's dead now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, not that I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you remember any other outings with your parents?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well we didn't go to seaside - no, not then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, but it were when I were working. Not 'til then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You didn't go away as a family when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, no. There wasn't the money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you go out anywhere at all on Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Good Fridays we used to go to - Oakham Hill. Holcombe. Yes, yes, go there. Good Friday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was there the racing there in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, not then, no. Not 'til later on - a long time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 It was just a day out in the country was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How did you used to spend Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, we used to go walks. Yes. All round country through the jungles and all round Turton and all up Edg
worth and - we've gone all over - Affetside you know. We've gone round Affetside and summer nights at twelve o'clock at night - and walked right round - me mother and neighbours when it - eeh they've not gone to bed 'til two and three in the morning or fo
ur o'clock. When it was summer evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 That's when you were older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 About how old would you be when you started doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh, I couldn't - I'd be working. I would, yes. They used to be lovely summer evenings then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How did you spend Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, we used to go to Sunday school and change our clothes when we come in and we' go walk, you know, but you never sit in your clothes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You had your special Sunday clothes just to go to Sunday school in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you go to church at all as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. At night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you change back into your Sunday clothes for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you play games at all on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your parents think it was wrong to work or to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 To work as well as play on Sunday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 They didn't work on a Sunday - not them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your parents attend a place of worship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. They - well, me mother did, I don't know about me dad. But me mam always went to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What denomination?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Church of England. Bradshaw church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 She went every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. More or less, me mam. Well, she was in choir at one time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you go as well to Bradshaw church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes. Yes. And then I've gone to parish church in town and I've gone - a I got older, I've gone to Victoria Hall, I've gone to }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1995576\charrsid2687195 Methodist}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 , I've gone all over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you were a child you went to Bradshaw Church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, went to Bradshaw - yes, yes. And then as I got older I went meself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were there any Sunday school outings that you went on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 They didn't have a field day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
No. Oh yes, they always had a field days. And we used to have a tea and had a field as we played in, you know. Run - running, games, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you have a band?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Yes. Bradshaw band. You have the band as they used to practice down Rigby Mission at one time - you had a place there and - Hardcastle used to give money towards that - yes. Him as owned the croft at one time. And - he married the 
Vicar's daughter - Judson. But they - they parted after a while, I don't know what went wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What other social activities were organized by the church that you took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, I only went to field day because they didn't have a great lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did they have any other activities at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 They might have had - concerts, you know, now and again, at Sunday - through Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you go to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No. Our David's gone in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did the church run a temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 They had a - well, I used to go to Rigby Mission Band of Hope.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you were a child was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. And - they used to have - the Lancashire dialect said in the church Band of Hope, they had
 a Band of Hope and sometimes I went there. The one did Sunday school, you know, at Bradshaw - yes, Bradshaw church, and a friend of mine as I - she lived in King Street - she used to do the Lancashire dialect. Yes. At the Band of Hope.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was this put on as a sort of entertainment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, yes. Yes. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Can you remember any other activities that it had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. Only billiards for lads, you know. Snooker, I think, billiards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was that organized by the temperance club or by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I think it were Sunday school, yes, got it all up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you belong to any other club organized by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was grace said at meals in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, more or less, they used to do. Nearly every family, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 And it was so in your family was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Who was it that said grace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Mum - me mother more or less, you know. Me dad didn't bother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, we just said our individual ones, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you know why that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, I don't. He didn't take interest in a lot of things, me dad. He were more for going on farms and working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would he vote at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh, aye, yes, he voted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you know which party he would vote for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I don't know about me dad but I know me mam were a Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did she take more interest in politics than him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. She didn't take interest in 'em but she - she'd vote for Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you know why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Why? No, I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
In some places in those days people felt that they might risk losing their job or their home if they voted differently from their employer - do you know if your father felt himself under any pressure?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Eeh, me dad wouldn't be under anybody if he didn't want, I'll tell you. He had a mind of his own. No. No, me dad could get work anywhere really. You know. If he chucked a job up he could get wor
k. And he worked hard. But there wasn't a lot of money attached to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you remember either of your parents being involved with a political party at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did they do anything to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Your mother didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 She just went along and voted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When your parents were not actually doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, sometimes me auntie would come and - and me mother would happen go to me aunties, you know, up -
 you see, she had two sisters lived quite close by.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Well, not - she'd go down to me grandma's, you know, and that's all, you know. And we used to go like in school dinner hour and collect her herbs in field at back you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 For your grandma?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your mother belong to any group of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 She used to go to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Mothers union or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I think she used to go to mothers union at one time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You don't remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You don't remember her belonging to anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did she ever go out just to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh as we got older she'd go to pictures in town. When we were working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Who would she go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Her sisters. Two sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What time did your father get home from work in the evenings when you were younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Half past five - to six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How many evenings would he spend at home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, he always used to come home but he'd go out again and have a drink if he felt like it, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would this be often or only now and again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No - sometimes he'd - he'd go onto farm if it were hay making and do hay making you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 He'd go to the pub now and then would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did he go to any club of any sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No, never - never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would you say that he went to the pub once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh, many a time - I - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 He went quite regularly to the pub - did your mother go as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did he ever attend the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Or bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. That were one thing he never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your father and mother belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Not for clothing or sickness or funeral - anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, you know, they used to have the Prudential club and all them kind, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 The insurances?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, the insurance. They had them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How did you get on with your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh, we had our ups and downs like everybody else but
 I did get on - on with 'em who we grew up, you know, what I mean but you know how you scrap over things when you're little. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You had your little squabbles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, yes. But - oh they didn't bother me - I used to get on with me work and they'd go fishing and go out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was there one of them that you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, I used to bother with our Fred more than Tom. Because our Tom wasn't like me and our Fred really. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Had Fred got interests you felt you could share?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 And 'course our Fred - after war he had asthma and I were always doing for him. He had asthma about twenty odd years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Younger did you feel -?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, I bothered with them both but I had more in common with our Fred - he were more like me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 As a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Different ones about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You didn't play with your brothers much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, in King Street like off Lee Gate, up the back
 - there were a big square where we could play - where they used to put the washing. And our Fred had his greenhouse at back there on his garden as he grew older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you play in the street or in other children's homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, in the street. And we used to have big bonfires when it were bonfire time on that square.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Top and whip. And we used to have them bowls, you know, them wooden bowls and we used to play jacks and bobbies and - you never see them now. You don't
 even see 'em playing top and whip. Skipping rope. Oh, used to play all sorts - us. We used to make our own fun. Play house and shop. We used to chop brick up and make it for sand like, you know. We've had many happy hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh, I did - me mother didn't bother - she did washing any time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were you free to play with anybody you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would there be anybody that your parents might discourage you from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, not that I know of - I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you belong to any youth organizations other than the church activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you have any hobbies when you were still at school - like keeping pets or collecting anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, I didn't, but as - we grew up I used to do crocheting and all like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was this after you'd left school? Or while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, no, it was after I left - after I left. We used to - do them silk jumpers and all sorts. Camisoles - we use
d to crochet tops, you know, for camisoles. And we used to sew our own clothes - underclothes - nightdresses. After I'd got yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What did you do when you were still at school - was there any special interest?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Your brothers went fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you ever go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, once or twice and then I shouted you talk too much - you'll never - I'll never get fish. You have to be quiet you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you go for walks much when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, we w
ere always going walks. Up the fields and play in water. There were a brook you know ran at back of me grandma's. We used to catch tadpoles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you ever do any bicycling when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Who did you go for walks with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Me fr
iends that I knocked about with like. There used to be a girl, Agnes, and I've gone with her. And - I've gone with Maggie - that young woman. And we've gone through jumbles and all round. All Affetside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was this when you were a bit older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you were a child did you take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you ever go to a theatre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, we used to come to town and go to musical halls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When I - no, not as a child. As we got older. Yes. When we were working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you go to concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, if there were any concerts on at school. You know, at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was this when you were a child and when you were older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would there be a music-hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, a theatre they used to have musicals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Musical comedy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, yes. Like -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I mean a music-hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Well, I used to go to Victoria Hall - they used to have concerts and we used to pay tuppence and they used to have 'em at Saturdays - Saturday nights. They were really good concerts then - them days - for tuppence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you ever go to the cinema when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well - I were older.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You were working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. When I did start going into town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Where would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, we used to come into town. 'Cos there wasn't any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1995576\charrsid2687195 till}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195  later and then they built one at top of where I told you - Scopey Lane. We - what did they call it - Scopey Pictures I think. Me mam even went to that one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 But this was later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes. Later years, but it's pulled down now and there is two or three bungalows built there. At the terminus where it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you were a child did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well - if I were going anywhere she'd say - give me a shilling-and sh
e'd say if you don't spend it bring it back 'cos it were needed, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you get a small amount regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, no. Not them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 It was only for special occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 And then you got -?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When I were working I got the shilling. They used to give us a penny to shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 A penny in the shilling when you were working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1995576\charrsid2687195 
And - I know I started - like I were a weaver at beginning and - and then - and then I - I used to sweep under the looms for me auntie and she used to give me a shilling for doing it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Well I saved that shilling up and then when I'd got enough at - holiday time I used to let me mother go to Blackpool with the sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How old would you be when you were doing this sweeping up for your auntie? Was it after you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh, I'd been working, yes, a while - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 It wasn't when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, no. When I were working meself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you got this shilling to go off somewhere if you did spend it what would you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, happen toffees or - it we went in anywhere, you know, or a cup of tea. Because I mean there were really nothing. Not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did anyone outside the home help your mother to look after the house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Not relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What about if she was ill - how did she manage then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Oh, well, they all the neighbours used to help them days. One would bake bread, one would do your washing and one would look after, if they had any babies, they'd look after them. Oh, they were good neighbours them days. Not like today at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Can you remember what happened when your younger brother was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, I don't remember it - I don't remember. Only they used to have the children at home, I do kn
ow that. And one would do like the baking and one would look after them and one would do washing. Not going in hospital. Well in fact me mother used to bring 'em in the world and lay 'em out. When they died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Can you actually remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did she do this fairly regularly for people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, if - they come and asked her, you know. Mother used to do it. 'Cos there wasn't like midwives and all that like there is proper today.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Why do you think it was that your mother was called on to do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
I don't know. Because she could do, yes, I suppose. And I think a sister of hers used to go with her. Oh, I've done that you know - I've brought them - helped to bring 'em in world and done }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1995576\charrsid2687195 
for 'em}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195  - I've done that-myself. I've been with me next door neighbour a few times. Well, in fact, she calls me her second mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How old would you be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I don't know - I been living in Webster Street then. And twins -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 After you'd been married a good while was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. Yes. Oh it were really through her mother letting her down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby apart from your grandma?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Her sisters. Oh well, there were me dad's side. They'd be Turton Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Fairly near as well then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How much did your parents see of them? Did they see them fairly frequently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, yes. Yes. And I used to go regularly to me grandmothers in Turton Road from school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your parents see their relatives at the relatives home or did the relatives come to your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
No, me grandmother Greenhouse I don't remember her coming a great lot but - my mam used to go - and me and she'd take our Tom and Fred sometime. But they didn't like visiting. Now he doesn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your parents have friends as well as relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. Me mam had a lot of friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Where did they see their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 They used to come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your parents go to their houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your parents share the same friends or did your mother have her own and your father have his own?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, yes, me mam had her own and me dad used to go with his, you know, like. The men, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did they have joint friends as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. He knew nearly everybody as me mam knew because they lived in same neighbourhood, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were friends invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would they be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well - more or less, we always made them a drink or a piece of cake you know. What we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would it be on particular days or occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, not me auntie - one of her sister's used to come regularly at Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What about the friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh, they used to just bob in and especially when we lived on Affetside - we never were wit
hout company there 'cos it were outing and all for them, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were friends actually invited into the home fairly frequently or did they just call in casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. Oh they'd come any time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Whether they were invited or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would you say that the friends who were invited into the home were your mother's friends or your father's friends or both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, they'd be both.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What about neighbours - did they used to drop in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would they ever be invited in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would they be invited in for a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh no. No, they wouldn't stop for a meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You said about making your own amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What did you think your parents did when they got together with their friends - how would they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, they used to talk, you know, and then - when me mam and - went out she used to with her sister to pictures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you think that when your parents got together with their friends they perhaps played games as well as talk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh no. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 They wouldn't play dominoes or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
No. Well, me dad might in pub I don't know - but I doubt me dad did it, but our Fred did. He went to Conservative club and played there. When he got older. When he were working. Me dad wouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You think your parents would just talk with their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Me dad didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Many people divide society into different social classes - in the time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to on
e class and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. Oh yes. Them with money. They always thought they were above you. Oh yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What classes would you say there were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, like you know there was people as had money and then you worked kind of t
hing for 'em, well they used to think they were more than you, you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you mean that you think there were just two classes of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. The rich and the poor. Yes. But - it's not like that today but they are more snobbish I t
hink today. I do. They're all for self today - don't you think. They didn't help - they wouldn't help you like they have in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Which class would you say you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, poor. Because we had to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What sort of people belonged to the poorer class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Well, it were good people. They weren't any kind of people, you know what I mean. They were down and out, you know what I mean. They worked for their living but they weren't as well off as them with the money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would you say that they belonged to a different category of people then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, well, they thought they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I mean the people who were more down and out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Them as worked kind of thing and they hadn't the fancy homes. Well, they didn't have fanc
y homes - not them days because it were all stoning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Stone floors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Yes, stone floors and you'd stone round with the white stone or a cream and - there were no carpets like there is today. You might have a - a rug as you'd made, you know. They used to do that in dark nights - making rugs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What sort of people would you say belonged to the richer class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, I can't really say but - they more or less had the money, you know what I mean. It - it'd been handed down and left to 'em, you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You can't think of any particular categories of person who would?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Well, it - like these with the shops and - and landlords and all that, you know. Now, I used to know some belonging to Reg as lived up Turton Road. Hamers they were called. And they had a shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What class would you put them in?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Well, they weren't without money. Because Reg's mother once asked me did I know of 'em, that's how I come to know about them. Oh, I said, I knew 'em well. I said, in fact our Fred and Tom used to call Jack - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1995576\charrsid2687195 Reggie's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195  cousin Jack - Uncle Jack they called him. Because we used to go to the shop, you know, when we lived in Turton Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently form people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were you ever told to curtsey to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Or to show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh well, we had to respect everybody really, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1995576\charrsid2687195 Was there anybody in particular that you had to be especially careful to show respect to?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. Not - because we always had to have manners. Me mam taught us them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was there anybody that you had to call Sir or Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you remember people showing respect to your parents in particular ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 In the district where you lived who would be considered to be the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, I don't really know as - don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You think everybody was pretty much on a par?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. On a level, you know. Because, I mean, more or less, they all worked. And I don't call 'em well off if they have to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You've mentioned }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1995576\charrsid2687195 Reggie's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195  family who had the shop - what sort of people would they associate with as friends? Would they associate with like your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, they always spoke to all - and that. Oh, they weren't funny people - no. Speak to everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What about the clergy - who would they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, Mr Judson used to come and visit everybody. At one time. Always come down to door - to houses and visit you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Who do you think his personal friends would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Eeh, well, I don't really know, no, I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Have you any idea who the teachers would have as their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What do you mean - the weekly schoolteachers or - well, I knew them well because they l
ived in village, you know. They lived down where Mission was. Edith - Naylor and - Edith Jarrod and Annie Jarrod - they were teachers at Bradshaw school. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1995576\charrsid2687195 
And then there were Miss Higginson - she lived on Tompe Moor and Headmaster lived on Tompe Moor - he were a Mr Grimes.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did they associate freely with the people round about?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Well, I don't think so. They thought they were a bit above, you know. They'd speak happen if they saw you but that were it. And isn't it funny, me cousin Ethel - goes to on
e of Haylors. Oh they were all good teachers - they were. And Mr Grimes was a good Headmaster. In fact they used to come from Longside school to take their exams at Bradshaw.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You'd obviously have farmers round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, I went wit milk our Tom went wit' milk - Billings it were - and she married a Scocroft. Well Scocrofts had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What sort of people would the farmers associate with round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, they didn't go, out a lot - they all bothered with other farmers really, you know, b
ut they didn't go out a lot unless they're go out to shows. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Agricultural shows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Because they can't leave farms really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were there any employers about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Employers of people who worked in the mills or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1995576\charrsid2687195 Well, they were only clot}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
hed like you know, up there. And there were Turton Tower Mill - like -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did any of the employers live round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes - them as worked at croft all lived in village practically.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 The ones who worked there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I mean the people who employed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Was over them? Well, Hardcastle lived - Hardcastle lived in his house, you know, as he - when he were in it but you know it was years and years in Bleachers Association and he left and - and then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What sort of people would he associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Who - Hardcastle? Them wit' money. He had money you know, because that croft belonged to him and then he didn't give the water rights up when he give - the croft up - he didn't g
ive water rights up right away - he kept them. And used to have wild ducks on, you know, and he used to shoot them down and he used to give them to - his people, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Who do you mean by that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Aye. Yes. Why - happen bosses, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What sort of people would you say went to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well there were a lot of village people went, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would they be mainly working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would the farm families go as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, more or less for Pillings lot I think were Methodist. And then Howarths - \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 I don't know whether they went to church or not.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What about the teachers - did they go to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What sort of people would go to the Methodist or any other non-conformist church? Would they be the same sort of people or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh they were village - no, they were working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was there a Roman Catholic church about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. They came into town them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were there any Roman Catholics living up there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well there is now. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Quite a lot were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 And they would always come into town to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 They'd come to town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was there any sort of friction at all between the Catholics and the Church of England members?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, not that I know of. But they didn't associate with you like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 They didn't associate with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. Not - not like - the Protestants and Methodists, you know. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would you say that they belonged to the same working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, they were working class, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh, more or less, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would you say that there might have been different standards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, them as worked, you know, 
did happen after me mum - do washing and they'd both work, you know what I mean - husband and wife would work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 So that there was more money going into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Mm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would it be because they had bigger families or not necessarily?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Could you describe a family where the mother and father did both go to work? Was there a family that you knew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, I - I've forgotten their names but there were a few as - as did work. I can't think now what their names was but th
ey - they more or less did go out, you know, and they'd have somebody doing washing for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would it enable them to have any special - a better home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 A better - home - home - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would they spend the extra money on the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, because I mean there weren't real fancy homes then. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would there be any of them who'd get a better standard of eating of food for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh, I don't think so. I don't think so. They'd happen have holiday, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you think that one group felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 The money - like a bit more money - yes. They'd think that, you know. I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, I suppose they did, you know. Them as had a big family, you know. And them as hadn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You mean the people who had a big family would be considered to be rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 More rough than - I suppose. Although they weren't had to be, you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was there a distinction felt between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, I didn't hear, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You don't think that your father felt that he was a lower category because he was a labourer than if he had a trade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh no. No. No. Not me dad. No. No. Me dad'd show them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh no, me mam wasn't a funny person. No. She wouldn't treat anybody any different. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you think she saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Well, they weren't - they were respectable people, you know, although, in them days when me grandad were - he were a plasterer and painter and that - decorator. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15091632\charrsid2687195 
Now, they used to call it - they went on spree them days when he perry- when he'd had a drink or two he'd perry wherry his money, I've heard 'em say. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
But I can just remember him and he wore a brown velvet cap - that's all I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would you say that it was possible at that time to move from one social class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, I don't think they did do that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Can you remember anybody at all that did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 There were somebody now I've been and forgotten. And they - they said she were or a real lady but I can't think of her name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What sort of a person was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Nice person. No, I can't think of her name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was there any particular reason why people would call her a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, they had money, but she was a lady. Rea
l nice dressed. Never thought she was different. It was personality and not money that made her a lady. I've tried ponder while you've not been here you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 It doesn't matter if you can't remember just who she was if you can tell me something about the sort of person she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, she were nice. That's how I can describe her you see. And she were a - a really nice person, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 In any particular way was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, just herself, you know. But she were - there were no fuss about her. No I mean she used to dress very plain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What about a gentleman - can you remember anybody being described as a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. Not - not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You wouldn't have described these Ashworth brothers as real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, they were Quakers you see like. Quakers. His mother and father were Quakers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What sort of people were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, they - we didn't talk to them much. His mother used to go about on a horse and she had a riding habit. That's how she used to co
me down Burtenshaw Brew - down to the mill. She used to come on horseback. And she were only slim.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 It was their mill was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. But I never spoke to her. They didn't mix, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did they take any part in the community life of this place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I couldn't say - I never - I never saw 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 They didn't patronize the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
No. Well, I don't really - I never saw them there. But George and Arthur used to come to Bradshaw church. On the - they had this house at Burtenshaw - the spastics have it now, you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did they give money to the church - these brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. They helped a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 They actually ran the mill did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Well, more or less. 'Cos I don't remember much of his father being th
ere. It were always them. And I think more so Arthur - George I mean - not Arthur. More so George came to the mill. And when the war broke out the first world war I mean, they had huts built near the mill and they had refugees put in - put in them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 This was voluntarily done by them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Be done - yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were these from - refugees from -?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Abroad somewhere I think so. I can't - I can't just think now where they did come from but they had all these huts built down near the mill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you remember seeing a policeman around?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Oh, many a time at Bradshaw high. We had one we - they used to call Black Sam. But I never knew his name - and - he - he were a sergeant - he was at it for years the police station near Bradshaw church
 across - they had it Eatons because - I think son were called there about - and I forget girls name but we used to go to school when I did. Bradshaw.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 This one who was called Black Sam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Black Sam. He - a policeman. And he lived out alongside - near me aunt Polly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 So you knew two really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Why was this one called Black Sam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I don't know. I couldn't tell you. But he were a beggar to get, you know, people - like he'd pummel 'em, you know, and try to get a case.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 He was persistent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Policeman like. Whether that were a nickname - I fancy it were, you know we used to give 'em a lot of nicknames at one time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was he liked or disliked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No. He were disliked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 And how did you feel that he treated people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, I - they always give him a bad name - they didn't like him, in village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What about sergeant Heaton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh he were very nice - very nice they were a nice family really - Heatons. But they lived at the police station.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How did he treat people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, he seemed to treat 'em pretty fair, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your mother ever tell you when you were a child if you were naughty that she'd call the policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Many time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Your home was rented wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 It belonged to the croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 The croft - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you see anything of the landlord or the landlord's agent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
No they took it out of one of our - don't know it were Tom's wage - when he worked at croft. And then I think when our Tom left and went to working for Knowles, on railway, he - I think they took it out of mine. 'Cos I worked there after, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you live in a house belonging to the croft before any member of the family worked there or was your father working there when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Me dad did work there. In - the - what do you call it - they called it black gang.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What does that mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well - he were a labourer for them, you know, these like - as mended - their - machines and all that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Only Hardcastle - that I worked there - what - like he belonged to the croft, you know. Well, we used to see Hardcastle hunting and all that, you know. He used to have hunting lodge in the yard as you came up Bradshaw Road, I don't know whe
ther you've ever been - going by the Crofters, and it - he used to come in at the - like gateway and then he had a big yard as branched off when we were coming through to the croft and he used to have all dogs there - the pointers there, and he'd have bee
r and something to eat perhaps if they'd been out hunting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was this just him and his family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, they were all, you know, these local hunt, you know, yes. Oh I can -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was it master of the hunt or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, yes. And I think Cork's have it now - at Harwood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What did you feel about Hardcastle as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Oh, we never had much dealing because it was turned over, you know, to bleachers after, you know, when he sold croft rights but he never sold water rights. For a long time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you feel your landlord was a fair landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, you go - if you have anything to be done we used to get it done but they don't now. You we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You were satisfied with that side of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes. Oh yes. Yes. And the
y weren't dear you know. Well, they only went up during war to five shillings. It were three and nine when me mam went in. That double house in Lee Gate Lane. And she went in when our Tom went full time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, it were hard. They all had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What did you think about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Well, I mean wages weren't - what - what they are today by a long chalk. I mean when I were a weaver I were on two looms and we could only make eighteen shilling we were lucky if we did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you feel the fact that your parents had to struggle affected you in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, I daresay we'd have got more, you know what I mean, because as we grew older we wanted more of everything. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were you conscious of being deprived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Oh no - I - no, because me mother always bought us clothes every two years but we had to make 'em last, like I told you we had to take 'em off and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When I was asking you about new clothes I didn't ask you how often you used to get them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No. Well we used to get them more - more than not - every two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was it any particular occasion?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, it were just when she could afford like, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was there any occasion when your father was ill or out of work and the family budget suffered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Oh well, they were - in wintertime you know they were - out of work for - for frost, and they didn't get dole then. And me dad were one that first started to pay that tuppence ha'penny when it first started
, me dad was one of 'em. 'Cos everybody didn't pay it then. No. But - oh, they've been out of work for weeks and weeks on end when frost were bad - or snow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What difference did it make to the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, you see, my mother used to have to wash to keep us going, you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did she do more washing when your father was out of work than she did normally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes. Yes. She'd wash for people you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How did the budget fare?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was she able to make enough in washing to compensate for your father's money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Well, you see, everything were a lot cheaper them days than now and then, you know, they used to have a lot of porridge at one time. Like that lady at crofters used to say if they asked what were they 
having for their dinner, it were porridge, every meal. She were a - oh, she were a big. Oh, she were big - Mrs - what were it - Lee - Mrs Lee she was - and she was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 She was the one who kept the Crofters was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Oh, and she had it donkeys 
years and - everybody liked her you know, and - she used to tell everybody about that. It were porridge breakfast, dinner and tea, for them. Well they were - 'course she were older than us you know, a lot. And she'd be older than me dad I suppose. But she
 were a big woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 This was in her youth was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Yes. Yes. She said. And then, you know, flour were cheap, balm were cheap, eggs were cheap. Bananas were cheap. You could live a lot cheaper than what you can today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When times were bad did you ever get any financial help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 From any source?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
No. No, we had to work. 'Course like I say me dad could do jobs, you know, he could earn a bob or two anywhere oh a farm, as they say, you know. He could earn anything with being a labourer you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were you given lessons at all by one of your parents or a tutor or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Three. Three. And they'll not have 'em 'til they're five now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you first started what time in the morning did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Well, we lived quite near, you know, to the school - we only lived at Lee Gate Lane while school were just - you know where the church is - well, the school were there, next door as you might say. Well we onl
y - we were only like a row of houses between square and a row of houses.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 So it would only take you a minute or two?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What time did it start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What time did you come home dinner time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I presume you did come home for your dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What about the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well it used to be four and when you got in bigger classes it were half past four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What time did you start in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I don't know - I think half past one or two o'clock - I forget.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you did first start at three did you go all day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What kind of a school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, it were a good school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was it the church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 It would be a day school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. 'Course they had Sunday school there and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was it mixed - boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. Yes. But the boys had a playground of their own. Not like they do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You had separate playgrounds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Not the tiny tots, you know, the tiny tots were with the girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 In the classes were the boys and girls segregated into different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, they were mixed but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 On the question of school it was obviously only a few minutes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh, few minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would anybody go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. Well, your girls like as lived near.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You say it was a good school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 It was. Well in fact they used to come from Longside to take their exams at one time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I liked it - but I weren't brilliant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were you happy there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. Them were happy days really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh well - they were all good teachers, more or less. And Headmaster were a good one. But he had eyes in his back I 
think. He'd be writing on't' blackboard and he could just get his chalk and he'd whiz it and he'd hit right person as were talking. Yes, yes, yes. Oh he were, he were quick. But he were good teacher, he were a good headmaster. There were no - hanky panky 
with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you like him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. Oh yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15091632\charrsid2687195 
He lived on Toupe Moor and - Miss Higginson lived on Toupe Moor}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were the teachers friendly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 They were all - oh yes. Oh Miss Higginson were a good teachers and she'd talk to you, she was, but 
she were older like the headmaster. Now, Annie Jarrod and her sister - they were younger, if you understand, and Edith Naylor - they were all younger than Miss Higginson.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You say that Miss Higginson would talk to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you mean about personal things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, the work - you know, the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as being important in life, like manners and tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. We had to make stockings and all like that you know - we had to work and we had
 to learn to sew - used to make waist aprons and all like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How did they go about teaching you such things as manners and tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh, used to say - we had to say thank you and please and all that like you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What about tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Oh well, they always told you to wash your hands and do - you know - keep yourself clean. 'Course we were taught that at home and manners too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What about punctuality - was the school concerned about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh well, we was never really late because we lived near, you know, but there was a lot as used to go late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 And what was the attitude to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well - Mr Grimes would say they hadn't to come late, you know. And if they kept it up he'd - reprimand them, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were the teachers concerned at all about the way you spoke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Not really. I - I know - I'll tell you before I forget, we used to have a man came to learn us the violin if we wanted to play 'em, I could have bought one at so much, you know, a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was this in the normal school hours?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. But they went downstairs to learn. Them as -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 This was as an alternative to doing something else was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, yes. Anybody as wanted to learn violin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you learn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 If you did something that the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, we get cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was this the regular form of punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. I think they were better when they did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did they use the cane as a form of punishment every time that -?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, you had to do it two or three times, you know, what I mean, and then if you didn't do what you had to do well, they give you cane.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did they ever punish you in any other way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh no. No. Oh, sometimes they'd make you come out and stand in corner with your hands -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 With your hands on your head?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you have to write lines out or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, I never remember writing any lines. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Can you think of anything else besides?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 They might have kept us in from playing, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did the girls get the same punishment as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What sort of offences would merit getting the cane or having to stand out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, if you used back chat to teachers or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What would that be - would that be the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, you'd get the cane. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What sort of offence would you have to commit to come and stand out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, if you talked back - just same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How did they differentiate which form of punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 They didn't really - I think just depended on teacher how she felt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did they ever punish you for not being able to do the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh no. No. Well, I never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was it always for some form of bad behaviour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Behaving. Yes, more or less.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was it the ordinary teachers who carried out the punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, sometimes if they were boys and they were being really bad they'd send them to the headmaster and let them - him deal with them.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, they'd not time really - they didn't bother like they do now you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did they ever ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, me mam used to ask us many times. And then later on when you got older I went to - to night class to learn a bit of cookery like.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you were at school did your parents ever visit the school for prize days or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well I don't remember having any prize days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your parents visit the school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh, me mam went - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 For what sort of reasons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, if she wanted to talk to master - Mr Grimes over anything they could go, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 She did meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 And talk about your progress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes, sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 So really she did show a bit of interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did the other children come from similar types of home to yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, more or less, they were - there were no really rich people you could say. No Not them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were most of the people who lived round about there either working in the mill or were there any other farm labourers and people like that?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Mill. Crofts. Oh yes, there were farm labourers - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was it mainly that kind of person that would live in that district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, them as worked at croft and them as worked in mill lived round about, and farmers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would some of the farmers children come to the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, not - not as I remember. They had to be bad if they did, you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Get some special punishment do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh no. No. No, if they couldn't do the work - the teacher would -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You mean if they were having real difficulties the teacher would give them special tuition?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, would talk - she'd talk to them about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Not really. They all played together them days really. 'Course they used to make their own amusement them days, not like they do now.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were there any children who seemed to be left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, no - not unless - like if they'd been playing with you and they didn't just do what you say you'd say well
 we're not playing, you know, that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 And that would be just a temporary little thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes. Play again, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you go on to another school after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How old were you when you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Four - thirteen. And I went - I went half time at twelve and full time at thirteen. And me brothers tool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would you have stayed longer if you'd have the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You attended the night school for cookery - did you attend any other kind of evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I used to go to Band of Hope.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 But not formal education at night school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, no, no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, not really, because I weren't all that good, you know. But 
I am - better than some was and still there were some better than me if you understand because we had what they called an X7th class, and that were the main, if you wanted to take exams.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were you in that class or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. I - I got up to standard seven but I never took that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Well we learned didn't we, I mean, we were taught by - to reckon up and we were taught to do our exercises and all like that. I - I don't think they exercise like w
e did. And we always said prayers and sang hymns in the morning when we went to school. And Mr Judson, Vicar, used to come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did he give you scripture lessons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, yes. Now Mr Judson's daughter and Colonel Hardcastle married. But they parted - at one time. He died of gout.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 During that last year when you were at school on the half time system.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh well, I went to Bank Top that half day, that belonged to the weaving you see. That school - Bank Top. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 So you did in fact spend your last year at a different school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes, I never thought about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You say it belonged to the weaving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Well, I think it belonged to Ashworth's really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was it just for their workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. And then the Bank Top children 
- like over there - the village. They called it Bank Top. It's still going. 'Course they've built a lot of houses now like of everywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You think the mill owner was in some way connected with the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 As a benefactor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would he be one of the school managers or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, he'd have something to do with it. He'd happen give money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did he ever visit the school when you were in class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I don't remember - I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you were at Bank Top on the half time system, how did you feel about the half time system?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, I didn't care for Bank Top school at all. I - I don't remember much about it because I never took interest. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You didn't like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, I didn't. None of us did really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. But we just didn't like going. You see, we had to go with working at - that mill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was it because you felt under this compulsion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I think so. Yes. We had to go you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What were the teachers like there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Eeh, I couldn't tell you - I've forgot about them what - it were more me own school I took to, you know. I liked going to school, I liked going to Sunday school. And I used to go to church - I've gone all over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you feel that the half time system was a sort of natural link before going to work full time or did you feel that it was very hard?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, we thought we should be at home that half day instead of going school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you think you learnt anything during that year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I don't. No. Because we didn't bother you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were you attending mornings one week and afternoons the other?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What time did you start when you were working in the mornings and going to school in the afternoons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh well, we had to start at six you know at mill. We had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15091632\charrsid2687195 to get}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195  up at five 'cos you had to walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 This was a further distance to walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 We had - I came from Lee Gate Lane - we had to come all down Bradshaw Brow, if you know where it is, and go up - Oaks Lane it is
 now and straight over railway lines. Well, I think there's a bridge now. Well there were a bridge but we didn't go over the bridge we used to cross the railway lines and - we had to past a farm - it were Abbots then, Abbots Farm, and I think Hoddy's I di
d before Abbots and there we went right along and then we went down the Brow and then there were a bridge what we used to run under and down some steps and them mill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 And you started there at six o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What time did you finish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Well, we had to have our breakfast, you know, to - between eight and half past and then we had to have our dinner, I think it were twelve 'til one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What time did you have to be at the Bank Top school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Eeh, I forgot - whether it were nine o'clock when we used to go at mornings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 But when you went in the afternoons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I think we started two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Until four o'clock was it or half past?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, I think it were four o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 And then the next week you'd go to school nine 'til twelve would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Mm. We had to start work you know dinner time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 At one o'clock would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What time did you finish work then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Half past five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What about Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Eeh we worked at Saturday mornings - 'til twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
When you were on the half time system - the week when you went to school in the mornings did you have to go into work on the Saturday morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You had the alternate Saturday morning off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 This was really your first job then wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Weaving. And we had clogs and shawls.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Before you got this first half time job did you while you were at school full time did you do anything at all to earn a little money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. I used to take dinners before I went to w
ork like down t'weaving to me aunties - and cousins. I've gone with two baskets and two dinners beside in me hands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you get any - ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Coppers, yes - coppers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was that from your aunties and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 This first job at the croft I were going to call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. No, that were at mill - weaving mill with me first job. And then I went to winding and I was thirteen month at Eadley winding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 This half time job - this was in the weaving - how did you get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, we had to ask - go and apply like could we start, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you yourself go to ask?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. You had to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. We - and then, you see, I had the relations, you know, and they took me, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 They sort of introduced you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Well we had a watch house you see and you had to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You had to go through that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What exactly did you have to do in the job while you were still half timer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh well you had to learn the job, you know, and
 you had to shuttlecocks. I don't know whether you've seen a shuttle, have you. Well, you had to put these cups on and then thread it through two holes and - used to put them in like that when - the were finished, you know, weaving. You had to keep them u
p and then when loom stopped you see you had to change them and then there were picking sticks at that you see. I almost got out with one but - yes - they say you know me and the weaver took it. That were the saying.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What were you paid as a half timer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Half crown.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you feel that was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Pretty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 It wasn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What do you think would have been a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well I don't really know because you know they didn't make a lot of money - not them days, b
ecause like I told you when I were on two looms I could only make - you were on piece work more or less. It were up to yourself what you got off in the course -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you were working your own looms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 But I mean when you were a half timer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, well that were just stationery what they give you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, it was half a crown?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Each time as you went half time. And then when you went full time you got five shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 And you say you don't think it was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, not for work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Not even considering what wages were in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You still don't think it was a fair one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, I don't, because you'd to do as much when you'd learned it as what weaver did. And then you had to clean looms, you 
know. You had to sweep under them and keep 'em clean, all that. I didn't think it were. I don't know what anybody else did. No, I think they got poor wages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you resent it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh no. I hadn't to do. You had to be thankful you got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you give it all to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
More or less. I used to save up when I'd - I used to sweep under for me aunt Ethel and - I used to let her save it for me instead of having it each week and then when I'd got enough I used to give it me mother to go to Blackpool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 For her to go to Blackpool?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Not me - her. With her sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you were a half timer getting half a crown a week did you give the half crown to your mother intact?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. Oh yes. You had to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did she give you some back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. If I were going anywhere she'd ask me did I want some.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What was it spent on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, if you were going on an outing you'd have to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 The money that you gave to your mother what was that spent on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What you mean - what I -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 The half crown.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh, it went toward keeping us - the food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you were still a half timer how did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 All right. 'Cos I knew 'em. On
e was me cousin and the other were - a friend as had - well, in fact - I don't know whether me mother didn't wash for her at one time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 They would both be older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. Oh yes. She were married. She were called Mrs Oak. And - and then w
hen I went to work at croft I went to work under her husband. Weren't it funny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 All right. 'Course you got a smack if you didn't do things right, you know, but then in weaving.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Who from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Them as was over you - as learned you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 The two that you were working with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I meant the people who owned the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh no. They didn't bother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you see anything of them at all while you were working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No. Very, very rare. He might come down and go in the office and that would be it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How did the bosses treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh they were very nice there - weaving bosses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How did you feel about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, I'll tell you this when I went to work in the croft I tol
d men there as I knew, I said, you don't know what hard work is, you lot. I said, you want go drive four looms 3/5 four broad looms, I says. You'd know what hard work were. 'Cos it weren't really hard in croft not - only for - carrying those copper roller
s like as they had the patterns on you know, for the cloth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How did you feel about your work while you were a half timer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh well, all right. Like when I was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you stay on at the mill after you'd done your year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, I - I 
had three - I had three looms when I left. I had to work the - good while - I can't just say but I know war'd broke out and I went to Eadley and I were there thirteen month when war broke out and I went to croft. You see, men were going up into war.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 So you worked at three places then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Your first full time job was at the mill where you'd been a half-timer?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you'd stopped being a half-timer and you went onto full time work what exactly did you have to do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Just the same - yes. Like, go for one missus, we called them missus's, and then go for the other. Half a day each. 'Til you got into it really proper and then you got your own two looms. And then you got three - if you stopped, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 And you stopped there long enough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. I had three. When I left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your attitude to job change at all when you'd become a full timer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, no. I liked really, only it was - it was interesting - weaving, but it got monotonous when you kept havin
g your ends broke out. They called 'em smashes. All your ends would come out, you know. Sometimes it would be a shuttle rough you know, sometimes it would be something wrong with your loom, see. You'd have to go for tattler to have it mended, you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 So you left because you got fed up with the tattler because he wasn't very good?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You were paid five shilling when you first went and then when you got your three looms you were paid - ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 According to what you made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you'd got as far as two looms you were earning about eighteen shillings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Sixteen to eighteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 And about what would you be earning when you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, it could - it just depended, you see, how you got your work off - they called them cups. You
 had to do so much and then you called 'em a quarten and you had to pull 'em off and pick them and take them into warehouse with a - a board - they called it a tally board and they marked on that, you know, what you' done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did the fact that this tattler wasn't very good mean that you weren't able to earn as much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 It didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
No, you couldn't earn what you really, like we - if you had some good looms and a good tattler you could earn more, you know what I mean. 'Course he was getting old but he hadn't same patience.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you were running your own looms were you still giving the money you earned to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. Oh yes. There were no keeping yourself them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did she give you some back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 The penny in the shilling do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 About how old would you be when you started getting the penny in the shilling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Eeh, I couldn't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How long would you have been working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 'Cos you see they weren't - all that well off if you understand and - really they hadn't it to give you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you were running your own looms how did you get on with the other people who worked with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You'd have somebody working for you then wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Didn't you have somebody like a half-timer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No. No, it were nearly all them as had four looms as did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How did you feel about the work when you were running your own loom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, I liked it - I liked it when 
I were there. I didn't dislike the weaving but if - if I'd had better looms and a better tattler I'd have been more satisfied.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you went to Eadley Mill were you weaving there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, winding - hank winding - hank winding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you work the same sort of hours there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes, we had to start at six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What were you paid there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, it was piece work there. Well it was something similar - sixteen to eighteen shilling you could make - that were hank winding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you feel that was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Well, when you have the very fine work it were hard work but you used to have a lady help you - used to come and help you out. You know. But it were - it used to get knotted and tangled and - oh it were a mess sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How did you feel about that work compared to the weaving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh, I didn't like it like weaving really. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How did the employer treat you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh he wasn't bad - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I weren't struck on him - but he were all right but I weren't struck on him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How did you get on with the other people there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Oh I got on fine with 'em. Not a great while since I saw one as used to help us Polly - I saw her - I met her up at Tynleys - she was visiting her sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You stay long at Eadleys did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
No, I only stopped there thirteen months. And war broke out and I went to - the croft - well it were only ten minutes away from our house to go home to \{ILLEGIBLE\} dinner.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was it because of the war that you went to work in the croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Yes. Yes. Because I could got a job, you see. Through the men going up to the war. Oh they were particular, you know, who went and who didn't at croft. You had to be relations at one time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 If you'd have been able to go there in the first place would you have done so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, I don't know. I wanted to go to weaving. 'Cos somebody else had gone as I knew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 And it was relatively easy to get into weaving but not into the croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you were working at the croft what exactly did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Well I went in - eeh, what did they call it - it were up at beginning end - eeh, now what do they call that - then I came down from there into white side. And we - I used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was there bleaching at some stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. The - at the beginning end - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 It was something to do with bleaching that you were doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes. Eeh, I just can't think what it were called - that. They had a name for it, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Well it were more or less plating down and - and sewing. Like you got two pieces of your cloth - and - there were raw edge, you know, and you just sewed them together. And you used to have to pull your machine to these big - wagons. They were 
roped, you know how they - have you ever seen them in the croft - well, they loop it kind of thing and do it all round in like the back croft and it comes down to where I work in - in the white side. And it were like in what we used to call the rope. You 
see they looped it - this - they had a was of doing it you know and it were wet from the wet croft you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was this when it had been bleached?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was this what you were doing at the beginning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. And then - like - it used to 
come off those wagons. Well we had to sew these ends as were hung out - they used to pull these knots out what we had to sew - and - and then it went over a machine and it comes straight out of the roll and we plated it down like that. On the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What smoothly do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. On the wagon and we used to have to watch it. And we used to have to sew and all - these knots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 When you first went to the croft you worked sewing pieces of cloth together to be bleached?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, it was bleached. Yes.
 It was bleached. In the wet cloth. And it came down to us bleached in the rope and it had to be plated down - what they called plating down. It - you see, it come over a mangle through - rollers and onto this wagon and it were straight - like a straight 
piece of cloth, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 And had these pieces of cloth been sewed together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
We had to sew these knots as they're pulled out in wet cloth. They pulled them out on one side and we had to sew them. But they were sewing machines as you could pull 'em....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You had to sew and you also had to smooth the cloth out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Yes, yes. And watch it - press it down. And if there were any - what do you call them - brackoil - you pulled it out at side for it to be cleaned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was this the sort of job that you went on doing all the time you were at the croft or did you go on to doing other jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, I went on the tins - what they called on the tins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What did you have to do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Just same - it were white going through mangle and that were breaking down. But some of that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 So it was the same sort of work really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. But some of that were starched.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 It was a stage further on but you were doing the same thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes. Yes. But on that we got paid so much a week. Now on 
that - the whites side we made our wage. And when war were on they give us a war bonus of two pound. Well, they told us they could take that off us any time on piecework.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You were on piecework at the beginning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, on the other at the beginning - as they give us so much a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 A regular wage at the beginning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 And you had a bonus?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, on the - piece work. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 So you only got the bonus later on during the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How long were you on this first job on the whites side?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 In tins - on the tins it was as I worked for that lady's husband and then I went to work for his brother in the whites sided. Two Mr Oaks.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Which did you do first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 On the tins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Before you went on the whites side?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Whites side. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I thought it was the opposite way around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. What they called it tins - on the tins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What were you paid while you were working on the tins?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Eeh, I can't just tell you. I've forgot what wage were. Can't think what we
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Can you remember what you got while you were on the whites side?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Oh well, sometimes when we'd made a good week we could get - three to four pound with that bonus, you know. Now when my cousin Ethel were working at that croft she said it took them all their time to get three pound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was that before you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
If you got about four pounds on the piecework including your two pounds bonus - would you possibly be getting about two pounds when you were on the tins then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, we might have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would it be more than the eighteen shillings that you'd been getting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, it were. Because you see we were doing all right then at croft, you know, they had plenty of work with war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you feel that you were paid a fair wage there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you still go on giving the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Oh yes. Well, like our Tom had gone to war. Well, she hadn't his wage and - and then eventually our Fred went when he got eighteen they constricted 'em at eighteen you know. They had to go. But our Tom didn't - he went on his own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your mother still give you penny in the shilling back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What did you do with it - did you still go on saving it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, we didn't go out a lot because it was black-out you know. And then we weren't - used to coming in to town a lot you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How did you get on with the other people that worked at the croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh, I liked - I used to like them. 'Course I knew them more or less you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How did you feel about the employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh well I knew him - he lived at back of us and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you like him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, oh yes, I could talk to him. And I knew his sister and she worked under him too. She were tea ganger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you feel he treated you all right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh, I could talk to him - I didn't bother. Oh yes, he treated us all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How did you feel about the work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh I liked 3/8 did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you like it better than the weaving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was it more interesting? Was it because it wasn't so tiring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Mm. No, it wasn't as trying - you weren't bothered about it like you were \{ILLEGIBLE\}
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What jobs have you done since the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well I were there thirteen years - at croft and then I got
 - I went - I were about twenty-nine when I got married. Well then that girl as got my job - she got hurt so me boss came and asked me would I go back. Well I went back for about six weeks. And that were it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 And you haven't worked since?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. I'v
e washed - for a friend of mine as lived near me. I washed for her mother and her brother. And that - I cleaned for that friend and I went to see her in hospital not so long since, about a month back. She were in a wheelchair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would you have preferred any other type of occupation to weaving or being in the croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No. No. Well there weren't a real lot when we were - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Which of the work did you like the best?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 At croft. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you serve an apprenticeship - a training period - for any of the jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you belong to a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. General Workers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You didn't belong to the weavers then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No, I never went in weavers. I were always in General Workers Union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was there no restriction placed on the sort of union you could belong to in different jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Was it common in the place that you worked for the people to belong to the General Workers Union rather than to the weavers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. Me husband were in it. Me children were in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you take part in any of the Unions activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Did you feel that the workers and the employers had the same interests or that there was an element of friction at all between employer and worker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 I don't know, them days were different someway to what they are today. You were happy in your work them days. I don't think they are today.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What did you feel about the actual conditions you worked under?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh well they were all right. We used to say it were going home from home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 At the croft was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did it apply at the weaving as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
No, no. The croft. Because the bosses talked to you and all that you know. 'Course we used to have our breakfast there. We started at six. We h
ad eight to half past for breakfast. Oh yes, they were all right bosses. 'Course they were village people you know what I mean. You know them more or less.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you feel there were divisions of interest among workers in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Some people say that there was a great division between trained craftsmen and labourers or other types of workers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh well, they did - them as had the trades thought they were it, you know what I mean. You were only a labourer kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 In your particular working experience did you feel that there was this division of interest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, not in croft really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What about in the weaving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh well, I didn't particular take a lot of interest like over anything like that. But
 - I always got on with everybody, you know. But - like the printing was the - the trade in the croft really - where they printed the cloths - these. Them were on - rollers, you know, the patterns.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did the people who were doing that seem sort of different at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh no, I always got on very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 They associated freely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Would you say that your work changed your general attitude to life at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What do you mean? Since I left or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Or while you were still there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh no, I were no different than - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You don't think it's influenced your way of thinking at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh no. Only as I told men they didn't know what hard work were. No, I used to tell 'em. 'Course I knew a lot of 'em you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 After you started work you obviously continued to live at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. I were at home when I were twenty-nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did starting full time work change your relationship at all with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Or with your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you spend your Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. Went to Sunday school and we used to go up church and sometimes we'd go - go to Victoria Hall. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15091632\charrsid2687195 Sometimes we'd go to King's Hall and sometimes we'd go Methodist sometimes go -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you take any interest in politics yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. Never.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you mean you never even voted at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh I have, yes, I voted but I mean I never -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you vote at the election in 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Can you remember what party you voted for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Conservative I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Do you know why that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh, me mother were one and that were it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you ever feel under any pressure from anybody to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Were you a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you ever work for any of the parties at election time or any other time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 In your spare time after you'd started work you've already told me you started to do things like crochet work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 And that you sometimes went to musical comedies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15091632\charrsid2687195 They}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195  were treats. We used to go -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you do anything else differently from what you'd done as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh no, not really. We used to go walks. Out in the country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You had these }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15091632\charrsid2687195 sorts}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195  of moonlight walks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 
Oh yes, yes. 'Course they were different days then. You know everybody used to sit out and talk to one another and - and - and then they'd say well we'll have a walk round and sometimes we'd go right round Affetside, sometimes Bradshaw Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 People would sit outside the houses in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes. Yes. You don't see that now. You don't mix like used to do them days. They don't. And especially in those places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 People are not very neighbourly now are they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 No. No. No. I heard a good one today about a person being on -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you make any new friends about this time after you'd left school and started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, I made one when I went to Eadley. She were called - eeh, now what were her name - she had a friend, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15091632\charrsid2687195 Honor}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195  Martin - Hetty Burry, she were called.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 You met her at Eadley?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 At Eadley. Yes. She were in the winding. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you make any other friends? Any boy friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh well, not really. When I went to croft I wrote to - a boy as worked with o
ur Fred - very friendly with our Fred - Harold Gallagher and he died - not - now - well it'd be twelve month or two years since. I wrote to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you take your friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. We used to always take our friends home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you have any special friend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well, I used to go out with a girl two years - two doors up - for a while. But she's in Liverpool now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Where would you go to with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh we used to go to pictures - in town. That were when we were working you know. In our teens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 She worked at the croft. Oh yes, she knew her - knew me mam because we only lived two doors. 'Course her mother came from Liverpool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your parents expect to know where you were when you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh yes. You had to tell 'em where we were going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Up to about how old did you have to do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well I always told me mother - so where I went I always told her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you feel that you had to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh no, no. No. I just did. No, I could talk to my mother - a lot of people couldn't - talk to theirs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did you have to be home by a particular time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well we always used to go to bed when we were working you know - we were all in for ten. Well they didn't stop up late in country 
really - they didn't. Because me mother -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Did your parents actually impose a time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Oh well, if we went out at weekend - yes. They'd say well we're not stopping up late, you know. Father never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 How long did that go on for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Well we 
never did stop out really late. Because if we went to Grand - when Grand were going - we'd go first house and then go home, you know what I mean. 'Cos they used to have two houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 What sort of transport was it them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Trams. Did you ever see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3959498 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, because they carried on in Bolton a long time didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380765 NR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3228260\charrsid2687195 Yes, they did. Yes, yes. Yes.
